list.name: Changes
list.comment: Wide-ranging house cleaning. Most all of this bils down to insufficient error messages in cases that a wrong argument, wrong number of arguments etc. were used. Now it gives much much better feedback on the type of error. Re-ran the parser

task.summary: Default task
Parameter was being ignored in certain cases, now it's not.
Cleaning up before a refactor.
Changes to Module state (so it uses the existing, tried and true stack machinery rather than its own stuff). CIL-1166 fix.
Lots of constructor clean up. Some tests fail but this is a good point to do a commit before the next phase.
Fixed a long-term state insufficiency. Does not effect anything current, but would cause problems later.
Found and fixed (I hope) a serialization bug if networks of objects had cycles (so somewhere in a network of object one of them eventually resolved to itself.)
Tinkering to get some edge cases post XML (de)serialization.
Still tinkering with some XML serialization. Doing a check in since there is an ice storm on the way and I want an offsite backup.
More XML serialization improvements. Base64 encoding (then decoding) things so any embedded XML doesn't cause errors.
VStack now used and tested. Capture before deleting a bunch of dead code.
More tweaks for XML serialization. Added ability to read PKCS 1 keys.
CIL--1193 support for CRT (Chinese remainder theorem) in RSA private keys. More serialization tests. Key tests too with new key pairs generated by Open SSL.
Added a bunch of XML serialization roundtripping to tests.
Added a coupel more tests. Tweaked serialization order for speed. Handled one legacy edge case.
Finishing up coding task. Test tweaks as I document.
Added some documentation for a QDL module. A few items needed to be Serializable.
CIL-1146 support. First cut is standard authorization.
CIL-1146. This required some small changes but mostly this was making sure the maven build would work.
CIL-1206 fix
CIL-771 support -- added grant type for token info.
CIL-771 support. Improved storing QDL state.
Small improvements for CIL-771
5.2.5 final checkin. Updated online help. Found an edge case where formatting a string lost a few linefeeds.
Creating 5.2.5
Bad version number in QDL pom.xml.
Merge from 5.2.5 branch. CIL-1225
CIL-1174. Use default Java trust manager as the default.
Support for SciAuth
Changed how debugging works so it is more modular.
Added module to QDL for basic set operations. Found tiny issue with test not running in certain cases.
Made sets support in QDL official with tests and documentation.
Needed to update size function for sets.
More set support tests. Found lots of cruft in the documents. re-ran the parser build.
Found and solved an edge case with lexical tokens in the parser.

Updated unit tests, added locking to cleanup threads. Rough count of QDL unit tests puts it at about 1875, in addition to many many for OA4MP. Lots of documentation upgrades/revisions. Parser regenerated.
Cleanup can now be disabled. Found and fixed another issue with the parser -- with regression tests.

Wide-ranging house cleaning. Most all of this boils down to rectifying insufficient error messages in cases that a wrong argument, wrong number of arguments etc. were used. Now it gives much much better feedback on the type of error. Re-ran the parsers to make sure everything was rebuilt with the latest version of ANTLR, since that has a few bug fixes that possibly (though very unlikely) could affect us.
Mostly getting ducks in a row before 5.2.6.
Some more cleanup. Haad to reorder execution of a few methods.
Removed some very dead code. Tweaked listing.
Finally reproduced really annoying terminal bug and fixed it. Also found one edge case for null arguments that was not handled.
More pruning. Twiddled exceptions to give better messages
More house cleaning and pruning. Added more tests for sets and beefed up serialization test so it is not haphazard. Added a complete set of server mode regression tests.
Cut out a ton of dead code and useless comments. Found edge case in parser, so re-ran ANTLR build. test included in case of regression.
